Writing a function for RMSE
rmse = function(x, y){
  sqrt( mean( (x-y) ^ 2 ) )
  }

fitlars <- predict(mod6, trainx, s=0.7878788, mode= "fraction")
rmse(fitlars$fit, qa$S_t)
[1] 0.06620859
a = 0
b = 0
for (i in 0:8){
  lb = 8*i+1
  ub = 8*(i+1)
  f <- fitlars$fit[lb : ub]
  t <- qa$S_t[lb : ub]
  if (which.max(f) == which.max(t)){
    a = a+1
  }
  else{
    f1 <- f[f < max(f)]
    t1 <- t[t < max(t)]
    if (which.max(f1) == which.max(t1)){
      b = b+1
    }
  }
}

print((a+b)*100/8)
[1] 62.5
sink("output.csv")
print(fitlars$fit)
sink()
